cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.MM 

This paper deals with content caching in wireless networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication technologies. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves machine learning techniques for content popularity prediction, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a utility maximization problem and uses regret learning, which are topics related to optimization and control, respectively, indicating a possible fit with cs.SY (Systems and Control) as well. Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed algorithm using simulations, which suggests a possible fit with cs.MM (Multimedia).
